<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="190" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.62/92: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-13T12:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">January 13,
                                        1920, noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    January 14, 2.32 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>123. Department’s 8 January 2, 6 p.m. Dresel will leave here Wednesday
                            evening [January] 14 with Dulles and three clerks. Dolbeare and Foster
                            are proceeding direct from Rotterdam. Dresel and Dulles will stop over
                            in Coblenz and reach Berlin Saturday morning.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>